CBRE is pleased to present for sale this strategically located retail investment opportunity incorporating a fully leased showroom to international longstanding tenant Reward Supply Co Pty Ltd, with future redevelopment potential.

We highlight the following positive attributes of this outstanding and rare investment and development opportunity:

- PRIME CITY FRINGE LOCATION ONLY 1.5KM*  NORTH OF THE CORE CBD
- WELL PRESENTED, FUNCTIONAL TWO-STOREY 861SQM* SHOWROOM & 180SQM WAREHOUSE
- FULLY LEASED TO LONG TERM TENANT REWARD SUPPLY CO PTY LTD UNTIL MARCH 2018
- 9 ON-SITE PARKING BAYS
- STRONG UNDERLYING LAND VALUE WITH FUTURE DEVELOPMENT POTENTIAL INCLUDING RESIDENTIAL, OFFICE AND MIXED USE OPTIONS UP TO 5 STOREYS
- PROFILE CORNER WITH EXTENSIVE 20M* FRONTAGE TO NEWCASTLE STREET AND 35M* FRONTAGE TO PALMERSTON STREET
- HIGH AMENITY LOCATION WITHIN CLOSE PROXIMITY TO HEART OF NORTHBRIDG FEATURING POPULAR BARS, CAFES, RESTAURANTS, RETAIL AND CULTURAL FACILITIES
- WELL SERVICED BY PUBLIC TRANSPORT (BUS & TRAIN) & CLOSE PROXIMITY TO THE PERTH ARENA
- SUIT INVESTORS, DEVELOPERS AND FUTURE OCCUPIERS

The property is being offered for sale by way of Public Auction to be held on-site on Thursday 27th October 2016 at 11.00am AWST.

For further information regarding the property, please contact the exclusive selling and marketing agent CBRE.

354 Wanneroo Road, Madeley, Perth, Western Australia.

CBRE is pleased to offer for sale Lot 13, 354 Wanneroo Road, Madeley (corner Gnangara Road), Madeley, Perth, Western Australia on behalf of the Deceased Estate (Administrator Appointed)

The lot comprises 19,152 square metres (approximately) and is zoned 'Urban Development' under TPS No. 2 within the City of Wanneroo with potential for R20 density residential development.

This offering provides a unique opportunity to acquire urban land within a built up area capable of immediate development

This property features; 
•	Immediate access to Perth train station, bus port and freeway
•	Central location 300* metres from heart of Northbridge and 500* metres from the Perth CBD.
•	Zoned ‘City Centre’ within the City of Perth 
•	4:1 plot ratio, with maximum 50% bonus achievable 
•	Versatile use potential (STCA)
•	Development scheme in place for 34-storey, mixed use project comprising 157 apartments, 180 car bays, 3 ground floor commercial / small bar
•	Unrivalled amenities in the immediate locality include retail shops, bars, cafes, restaurants, hotels, entertainment, sports arenas, education facilities and cultural amenities including the new and soon to be open $350M WA Museum.
•	Be part of the gentrification of Stirling Street boasting a host of recent high rise developments including: Verdant (137 apartments), Global Student accommodation (573 beds), Oracle (130 Apartments), Campus Perth (700 beds plus supermarket) all adding to the amenity and vibrancy of the precinct.

Offers to Purchase invited closing Thursday 2nd April 2020 at 2pm (AWST).

*approx.
